# VibeCraft — Epic Fantasy Knight Fighter (Anatomically-Principled)
#
# Generated applying medical anatomy principles for humanoid body continuity:
#   - Continuous body mesh with NO disjoint parts
#   - Proper joint thickness at neck, elbows, wrists, knees, ankles
#   - Smooth cross-section tapering following real anatomy
#   - Armor as overlay on continuous body form
#   - Contrapposto stance with hip/shoulder counter-tilt
#
# Medical/anatomical references consulted:
#   - Gray's Anatomy (body layer continuity: bone→muscle→fat→skin)
#   - Kenhub musculoskeletal system (bone-muscle-tendon connections at joints)
#   - Anatomy for Sculptors (proportional calculator, cross-section references)
#   - Proko anatomy courses (surface landmarks, muscle group volumes)
#
# Proportional system: Loomis 7.5-head canon
#   Head height = 0.27 units, total height ~2.0 units
#   Anatomical minimum thicknesses enforced at all joints:
#     Neck: ~0.08-0.12 radius (sternocleidomastoid, trapezius, spine)
#     Wrist: ~0.035 radius (radius, ulna, tendons, vessels)
#     Ankle: ~0.035 radius (tibia, fibula, Achilles tendon)
#     Knee: ~0.05-0.06 radius (patella, ligaments, cartilage)
#     Elbow: ~0.045 radius (olecranon, tendons, brachialis)
#     Waist: ~0.17 radius (abdominals, obliques, spine, organs)
#
# 1849 vertices, 3276 triangles
# Dimensions: ~2.0 units tall body, sword tip at ~Y=3.0
#
# Convention: Y-up, right-handed coordinate system

mtllib fighter.mtl

